app.cards

Enum Rank

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Rank>
      • app.cards.Rank
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Rank>

    public enum Rank
extends java.lang.Enum<Rank>
    Lists all possible card ranks and stores their human-readable names as well as an integer value to enable comparisons. Values start at 1 (Deuce) and go up to 13 (Ace).

      • fromShortcut

        public static Rank fromShortcut(char shortcut)
        Returns the appropriate Rank for the supplied shortcut, which is matched against the shortName property of the Rank objects.
        Parameters:
        shortcut - short name for which the Rank should be looked up (case-insensitive). Must be one of 'A' (Ace), '2' through '9' (Deuce through Nine), 'T' (Ten), 'J' (Jack), 'Q' (Queen) or 'K' (King).
        Returns:
        Rank object with matching shortName, or null for an invalid shortcut
